\end{equation}
This expression reproduces the $tt$-component of the Einstein field equations inside a spherical mass distribution when written in terms of the areal radius $r$.

The \href{https://willrg.com/documents/WILL_RG_I.pdf#subsec:pressure}{intrinsic pressure of the vacuum geometry (derived in WILL RG I)} is negative and proportional to its density:
\begin{equation}
P_{\Lambda}(r) = -\,\rho_{\Lambda}(r)\,c^{2}.
\end{equation}

The structural vacuum density $\rho_{\Lambda}$, when excited by the dynamic state of a stable galactic system ($Q^2$), identically reproduces the Newtonian halo density.
\begin{equation}
\boxed{\rho_{\text{WILL}} \equiv \rho_{\text{N}}}
\end{equation}

lemma.body:
