\boxed{\kappa^{2} = \frac{\rho}{\rho_{\max}}}
\]

To sustain a flat rotation curve with constant velocity $V$ (where $\beta = V/c$) at a galactic radius $r$ where baryonic matter is negligible, classical mechanics postulates a Singular Isothermal Sphere (SIS) with the density profile:
\begin{equation}
\rho_{\text{N}}(r) = \frac{V^2}{4\pi G r^2}.
\label{eq:newton_halo}
